{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, all researchers using gym-flp are encouraged to redefine the reward computation according to their respective needs and suitable for their problems in question.",
    "For instance, additional reward or penalty terms can be defined inside gym-flp.",
    "AgentThis package uses Stable Baselines 3 [59] as the framework for RL and the algorithms it currently supports (as of version 1.8.0).",
    "Thus, the algorithms available off-the-shelf in gym-flp are [45] • Proximal Policy Optimization (PPO) [61] • Advantage Actor Critic (A2C) [62] • Deep Deterministic Policy Gradients (DDGP) [63] • Twin-Delayed DDPG (TD3) [64], and • Soft Actor-Critic (SAC) [65] Prior to training, hyper-parameters for the algorithm are loaded from the algoconf.json file located inside./algorithm/config/.",
    "The hyper-parameters are the baseline values as stored in the Stable Baselines 3 classes."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "AgentThis package uses Stable Baselines 3 [59] as the framework for RL and the algorithms it currently supports (as of version 1.8.0).",
    "Thus, the algorithms available off-the-shelf in gym-flp are [45] • Proximal Policy Optimization (PPO) [61] • Advantage Actor Critic (A2C) [62] • Deep Deterministic Policy Gradients (DDGP) [63] • Twin-Delayed DDPG (TD3) [64], and • Soft Actor-Critic (SAC) [65] Prior to training, hyper-parameters for the algorithm are loaded from the algoconf.json file located inside./algorithm/config/."
